TERMS AND CONDITIONS
These are the standard terms and conditions that are referred to, and form part of, the Purchase Order between Axiom Group Investments Pty Limited trading as Axiom Group (Axiom) and the supplier noted in the Purchase Order (Supplier) (Purchase Order).
1. Definition In the Purchase Order:
1.1 Goods means the item(s) to be supplied by the Supplier set out in the Purchase Order (if any); and
1.2 Services means the services to be provided by the Supplier set out in the Purchase Order (if any) and any related services, functions or responsibilities not specifically described in the Purchase Order which are reasonably required for the proper performance and provision of such services.
2. Conflict The Purchase Order will prevail if there is any conflict between it and the terms of any offer or acceptance by the Supplier in relation to the Goods or the Services (or both, as the case may be).
3. Amendment Save as set out herein, the Purchase Order may only be varied, modified or rescinded by agreement in writing by Axiom. The parties acknowledge that no oral or written stipulation of the Supplier made prior to its acceptance of the Purchase Order shall be a term of the contract between Axiom and the Supplier unless set out in the Purchase Order.
4. Cancellation Axiom reserves the right to cancel the Purchase Order in whole or in part prior to the supply of the Goods or commencement of the Services (or both, as the case may be).
5. Acceptance The terms of the Purchase Order shall be deemed to have been accepted by the Supplier if it: 5.1 notifies Axiom (in writing or otherwise) of acceptance of the Purchase Order; or 5.2 does any act or thing pursuant to the Purchase Order.
6. Performance 6.1 The Supplier shall: 6.1.1 in the case of any Service, carry out and complete the Service in a proper and workmanlike manner; 6.1.2 in the case of any Goods, ensure that the Goods are fit for purpose and free from any defects; 6.1.3 supply the Goods or carry out and complete the Services (or both, as the case may be) so as to comply with all laws, by-laws and regulations of any governing authority or any statutory corporation or authority or any officer of employee thereof having jurisdiction with regards to the Goods or Services (or both, as the case may be); and 6.1.4 supply the Goods or carry out and complete the Services (or both, as the case may be) to the reasonable satisfaction of Axiom. 6.2 Any materials used by the Supplier in connection with the Goods or Services (or both, as the case shall be) shall be suitable and proper materials.
